guardsExecutors

private java.util.List<BTExecutor> guardsExecutors
List containing the IBTExecutors in charge of running the guards. The i-th element of this list manages the guard of the i-th child ( children). Note that if a guard is null, its corresponding IBTExecutor is also null.

guardsResults

private java.util.List<ExecutionTask.Status> guardsResults
This List contains the current evaluation status of all the guards. If a guard is null, its corresponding status is Status#SUCCESS (null guards are evaluated to true).

indexMostRelevantGuard

private int indexMostRelevantGuard
Index of the current most relevant guard. All the guards before it have finished in failure. This represents the guard such that, if its status changes to success, then it would be the one selected by the dynamic priority list.

Method Detail

internalSpawn

protected void internalSpawn()
Spawns the first child with active guard. It also requests to be inserted into the list of tickable nodes of the BTExecutor, since this task has to check its children's guards all the time. If there is no active guard, the spawning process is considered to have failed, so internalTick() will return Status#FAILURE. If some guards are still running the spawning process is not considered to have started yet.

Specified by:

internalTick

protected ExecutionTask.Status internalTick()
Checks if there is an active guard with a priority higher than that of the active child. If there is such a task, it terminates the active child and spawns the child of the guard with higher priority, and Status#RUNNING is returned. If there is no such task, then the status of the active child is returned.

If the spawning process failed, this method just returns Status#FAILURE. If the spawning process has not finished yet, this method keeps evaluating the guards, and returns Status#RUNNING.

Specified by:
internalTick in class ExecutionTask
Returns:
the status of the task after being ticked.
See Also:
ExecutionTask.internalTick()

resetGuardsEvaluation

private void resetGuardsEvaluation()
Resets the evaluation of all the guards. This method leaves all the guard executors ( guardsExecutors) ready to start again the evaluation of the guards. It internally terminates the IBTExecutor of each guard, creates a new one, and then ticks it.

evaluateGuards

private Pair<ExecutionTask.Status,java.lang.Integer> evaluateGuards()
Evaluate all the guards that have not finished yet, that is, those whose result in guardsResults is Status#RUNNING, by ticking them.

If all the guards have finished in failure, this method returns a Pair whose first element is Status#FAILURE. If guards' evaluation has not completed yet, the first element of the Pair contains Status#RUNNING. If all the guards have been evaluated and at least one has succeeded, the first element of the Pair is Status#SUCCESS, and the second one is the index, over the list of guards (guardsExecutors) , of the first guard (that with the highest priority) that has succeeded.

longTick

private void longTick(IBTExecutor executor)
This method ticks executor 20 times. If the executor finishes earlier, it is not ticked anymore, and the ticking process stops.

Parameters:
executor - the IBTExecutor that is ticked.
